window.bookSummaryJSON = "<i>New York Times</i> best-selling author Harry Turtledove has intrigued readers with such thought-provoking \"what if...\" scenarios as a conquered Elizabethan England in <i>Ruled Britannia</i> and a Japanese occupation of Hawaii in <i>Days of Infamy</i> and <i>End of the Beginning</i>. Now, in the first of a brand-new trilogy, he rewrites the history of the world with the existence of an eighth continent. <p>Atlantis lies between Europe and the East Coast of Terranova. For many years, this land of opportunity lured dreamers from around the globe with its natural resources, offering a new beginning for those willing to brave the wonders of the unexplored land.</p>"; 
